 on Lydia to save not just her reputation, but her way of life, before those clever girls reveal all her secrets in their novels. Unfortunately, she might be too late."--cProvided by publisher.10aBrontë, Patrick Branwell,|d1817-1848,d1817-1848vFiction. 0aMan-woman relationshipsvFiction. 0aGriefvFiction. 0aAdulteryvFiction. 0aTutors and tutoringvFiction. 0aMay-December romancesvFiction. 0aSelf-realization in womenvFiction. 0aYorkshire (England)xHistoryy19th centuryvFiction. 7aHistorical fiction.2lcgft 7aHistorical fiction.2gsafd 7aRomance fiction.2lcgft 0aLarge type books.  c(OCoLC)1201674220  c4670d4670